### Program to Respond to Dead and Distressed Marine Animals in the Pacific Waters
#### Solicitation Details

| Tender Status | Expired |
| Tender Closing Date | 2023-11-09T13:00:00 |
| Expected Contract Start Date | 2023-12-01 |
| Expected Contract End Date | 2025-03-31 |
| Contracting Entity | Fisheries and Oceans Canada |
| Contact Information | [Karine Plante](mailto:Karine.Plante@dfo-mpo.gc.ca), (506) 377-9127 |
#### Tender Description
The Department of Fisheries and Oceans Canada is seeking a contractor to support the Pacific Marine Mammal Response Program in Canadian Pacific waters. The program aims to:

* Coordinate marine animal response efforts to ensure all dead and distressed marine animal incidents in Pacific Canadian waters are reported and investigated.
* Respond, where possible and safe, to marine animal incidents, particularly those involving species currently listed under the Species at Risk Act (SARA).
* Provide response guidance to other authorized partners and maintain marine animal incident data to inform conservation measures and improve understanding of marine animal species.

The contractor will be responsible for rehabilitating injured marine mammals and ensuring that all marine animal incidents are reported, especially those involving listed species. The program also aims to improve communication with commercial fishers and the public regarding marine animal conservation.
